-- Colombian Stock Movers: Canacol, Grupo Aval, Grupo Nutresa
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-01-18T21:17:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-18/colombian-stock-movers-canacol-grupo-aval-grupo-nutresa.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  gained 1.3 percent to 13,467.99, while the
Colcap Index rose 1 percent to 1,613.67.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Calgary-based  oil
company  that operates fields in  Colombia , rose 0.6 percent to
1,615 pesos. The company drilled the Cachalote-1st Well in
southern Colombia with results expected in two to three weeks,
according to a regulatory filing today.  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores SA  (AVAL CB), Colombia’s
biggest banking group by assets, gained 1.1 percent to 1,200
pesos. The company is meeting with investors to evaluate the
possibility of an overseas bond sale, according to a regulatory
filing yesterday.  The company also created a Cayman Islands-based subsidiary,
Grupo Aval Ltd., without giving further details, the filing
said.  Grupo Nutresa SA (NUTRESA)  (NUTRESA CB), Colombia’s biggest food
producer, rose 1 percent to 21,000 pesos.  Global coffee consumption will grow about 1.5 percent this
year as a slowdown in economic growth fails to deter consumers,
Roberio Silva, executive director of the  International Coffee
Organization , said today in an interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
